x4freetext: Spin correlation measurements for p-3He elastic

x4codes.hlp: University of Wisconsin, Madison, WI, United States of America

x4freetext: Tandem accelerator laboratory.
Wisconsin colliding beam polarized ion
source.
Beam polarization reversed during each run.
Spin orientation of beam set using a Wien filer.
Beam polarization determined by p(pol)-alpha
scattering.
Scattered protons measured using silicon surfac
barrier detectors located symmetrically to the right
and left of the beam.
Data taken from article.
No reply from L.Knutson to author proof.
Updated to new date formats.
BIB updates.
Unpolarized target. Forward cell typically cooled to
150 K, backward cell typically cooled to 80 K.
Corrected for energy differences between forward and
backward angle cells.
Scattering angles corrected for small misallignment of
detector slit systems.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: For backward angles, errors consist of
statistical uncertainty only. For forward angles, the
uncertainty in energy shift is also included.
The is an additional overall normalization uncertainty
of 2% for E(p) <8 MeV, and 1% for E(p) >8 MeV
resulting from polarimeter calibration uncertainty.
Estimate of uncertainty in c.m. angle.
Estimate of proton energy uncertainty.

x4freetext: Polarized 3He gas in double-cell system consisting of
a glass optical pumping cell located outside a
scattering chamber and coupled to a copper target
cell.  Two cylindrical Pyrex pumping cells: one
producing polarizations in the horizontal plane,
the other in the vertical plane.  Base temperature
of scattering cells typically 125 K.
Corrected for background.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: Uncertainty dominated by counting
statistics, but include statistical errors in the
determination of beam and target polarizations.
Overall normalization uncertainties of 2% for E(p)
<8 MeV, and 1% for E(p) >8 MeV not included.
resulting from polarimeter calibration uncertainty.
Uncertainty resulting from choice of background
subtraction algoritm thought to be negligible.
Estimate of uncertainty in c.m. angle.
Estimate of proton energy uncertainty.
